# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev, or set these in your host (e.g. Vercel
# Project Settings → Environment Variables) for deployment.
# Public site variables are OPTIONAL and fall back to `site.config.ts` defaults.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ values are exposed to the browser, so never put secrets in them.

# --- Site identity (mirrors data/meta.yml for Edge/Client contexts) ---
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://jaeung.me
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_NAME=Jaeung Lee
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_TAGLINE=Software Engineer

# --- Google Analytics (unset ⇒ GA is not loaded) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# --- Giscus comments (all four required; any unset ⇒ comments hidden) ---
# Get these from https://giscus.app after enabling Discussions on your repo.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GISCUS_REPO=owner/repo
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GISCUS_REPO_ID=R_xxxxxxxxxx
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GISCUS_CATEGORY=General
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GISCUS_CATEGORY_ID=DIC_xxxxxxxxxx

# --- Guestbook (server only; both required) ---
# Create the table with `supabase/guestbook_comments.sql`, then copy these from
# Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API Keys. Never prefix the secret with
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ or expose it to browser code.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=sb_secret_xxxxxxxxxx
# Legacy projects may use SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY instead of SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY.
# Lets the site owner delete any message and post replies. Required for replies.
# Use a unique, random value of at most 72 characters. Never prefix it with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
# GUESTBOOK_ADMIN_PASSWORD=replace-with-a-long-random-password
# Optional: salt for the stored IP hashes used to rate-limit posting. Falls back
# to the Supabase secret when unset; set it to rotate the salt on its own.
# GUESTBOOK_IP_SALT=replace-with-a-long-random-value
